{"word":"δοιοί","slug":"δοιοί","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δοιοί</b></el> adj (doi os_h_on suff_acc pl) <p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>epic for <a href='S:δύο'><el>δύο</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>two, both</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>δοιά</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>in two ways, in two points</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>two-fold, double</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}